palace coup of 1762, Paul in 1801. A terrorist group killed Alexander III in 1881. This last incident was 
burned into the Russian public memory; it occurred on 1 March in the Gregorian calendar â€“ or 14 March in the 
Julian one. Shulgin noted with relief that Nicholas had signed his abdication on 15 March and not on the 
